posts.desc: The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG 'Cement’ 2016 was one of the original four colorways released in 1989. The sneaker features the original White, Fire Red, Black, and Tech Grey colorway, with the speckled Cement Grey accents that give the sneaker its nickname. Released during the 2016 NBA All-Star weekend in Toronto, the sneaker was also retro’d in 1999 and 2012. The 1999 and 2016 retros are the only models that feature the ‘Nike Air’ branding on the heel, just like the 1989 OG sneakers.
posts.name: air jordan 4 white cement

posts.desc: The 2018 edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Concord’ features ‘45’ stamped on the black heel tab—a nod to the jersey number that Michael Jordan wore upon his return to basketball following his first retirement. The rest of the build keeps the shoe’s signature details intact, including a white ballistic mesh upper, black patent leather overlays and an icy translucent outsole underfoot.
posts.name: air jordan 11 concord

posts.desc: The Air Jordan 3 Retro 'UNC' arrives in March 2020 as an homage to Michael Jordan's alma mater. The special edition presents university-inspired colors on its dual-textured leather upper and eyestays, with elephant print panels granting an iconic touch. Valor Blue hits both Jumpman logos on the tongue and heel while the visible Air unit in the midsole and rubber outsole wrap up the styling.
posts.name: air jordan 3 unc

posts.desc: Released in April of 2015, the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Metallic White’ 2015 offers a remastered version of the colorway first released back in 2000. The sneaker has a white tumbled leather upper with metallic silver and black accents on an ice blue translucent outsole.
posts.name: air jordan 5 metallic white

posts.desc: The Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Space Jam’ 2016 commemorates the 20th anniversary of the movie ‘Space Jam.’ Worn by Michael Jordan as a Player Exclusive (PE) in both the movie and the 1995 NBA Playoffs, the 2016 retro ended up being Nike’s largest and most successful shoe launch ever. This 2016 sneaker is a more faithful reproduction of the original PE than the 2000 and 2009 retros. The sneaker also swaps the traditional #23 for MJ’s comeback #45 on the heel, a first for an Air Jordan 11 retail release.
posts.name: air jordan 11 space jam

posts.desc: The Air Jordan 3 marked the debut of Brand Jordan's visible Air cushioning, elephant print, and the Jumpman logo. Falling in line with the 2003 retros, this 2011 iteration features a Jumpman logo in place of the 1988 OG Nike Air branding at the heel and tongue. Nike Air branding wouldn't return to the Air Jordan 3 until 2013 with a release appropriately named 'Air Jordan 3 Retro '88.'
posts.name: air jordan 3 white cement

sport.desc: The Nike Air Max Plus 3 ‘Triple White’ treats the retro runner to a pristine monochromatic finish. The uniform color scheme on the upper, constructed from mesh and synthetic leather with a distinctive TPU heel clip, is disrupted by retro Tuned Air branding atop the tongue and medial heel. A matching white midsole packs visible Air sole units in the forefoot and a large-volume Air bag under the heel, good for enhanced impact absorption and a smooth ride.
sport.name: nike airmax plus 3 triple white

sport.desc: To celebrate the 20th anniversary of the Air Max Plus, Nike released the Air Max Plus 'Hyper Blue' 2018. The sneaker features a mesh upper in a Hyper Blue color scheme with wavy black TPU overlays. The sneaker also boasts an elasticated lacing system for an adaptive fit, a padded tongue for comfort, suede and leather details along the mudguard and heel, and an Air Max unit in the midsole for responsive cushioning.
sport.name: nike airmax plus og hyper blue

sport.desc: Launching as part of the New York skate brand’s Fall/Winter 2020 collection, the Supreme x Nike Air Max Plus ‘Mean Green’ delivers a statement-making interpretation of the vintage runner. The sneaker features a predominantly lime green finish, accented with gradient orange and blue TPU fingers that spell out ‘Supreme’ on the side panels. A raised Supreme box logo decorates the tongue, while Nike’s OG Tuned Air branding appears on the heel overlay. A matching green foam midsole houses orange-tinged Max Air units and a TPU shank plate.
sport.name: nike airmax plus supreme green

sport.desc: When it came out in 2000, the Nike Air Presto was designed to be as light and comfortable as your favorite T-shirt, and the 2016 Air Presto ‘Triple White’ maintains the lineage with a lightweight, breathable mesh upper that allows for a sock-like fit. Lockdown comes from the midfoot cage and lacing system, and it all sits atop a one-piece midsole-outsole construction for super light support. The entire sneaker is cast in white for a classic look.
sport.name: nike air presto triple white

sport.desc: The Air Max 90 'Triple White' launched in January 2020, marking the classic silhouette’s 30th anniversary. Featuring a recrafted build inspired by the original 1990 release, the sneaker is dressed in an all-white finish that allows its clean lines to stand out. Details include a mesh upper with stitched leather overlays, TPU eyelets and an Air-infused midsole reinforced by a waffle-tread rubber outsole.
sport.name: nike airmax 90 triple white
